<seg id="33">The parallel audit of the sales tax administration in the Czech Republic and Germany was carried out on the basis of an agreement between the two audits.</seg>
<seg id="34">In addition to the focus ′′ exchange of information ′′ under Regulation (EC) No. In 1798/2003 of the Council and 1925/2004 of the Commission, other closely related aspects were also examined, e.g. the registration of taxpayers, tax returns and summary reports.</seg>
<seg id="35">In addition, the audit also covered the legal status of cross-border passenger transport by bus and the comparison of statistics.</seg>
<seg id="36">Comparing the VAT administration systems in the two countries, differences were observed in the following areas:</seg>
<seg id="37">1) Registration for sales tax purposes.</seg>
<seg id="38">While in Germany entrepreneurs are registered independently of the level of turnover, among others, the essential criterion for registration in the Czech Republic is the exceeding of the turnover threshold set out in the Turnover Tax Act.</seg>
<seg id="39">In the Czech Republic, taxable persons receive only one tax identification number, which they also use for intra-Community transactions.</seg>
